briefTitle: Safety Study of Ethinylestradiol/Drospirenone in Dysmenorrhea

eligibilityModule.eligibilityCriteria:
Inclusion Criteria:

* Patients aged 20 years or older at obtaining informed consent
* Patients having the normal menstrual cycle (25 to 38 days) in the latest two menses before the final enrollment
* Patients having a total dysmenorrheal score of at least 3 points in twice of the latest menstruation before the final enrollment

Exclusion Criteria:

* Patients with ovarian chocolate cysts
* Patients with fibroid needed to be treated
* Patients with estrogen-dependent tumors and patients with cervical cancer or suspected cervical cancer
* Patients with undiagnosed abnormal vaginal bleeding
* Patients with thrombophlebitis, pulmonary embolism, cerebrovascular disease, or coronary artery disease or a history of those diseases
* Patients aged 35 years or older who smoke at least 15 cigarettes per day
* Patients with migraine accompanied by prodromata
* Patients with pulmonary hypertension or valvular heart disease
* Patients who are regularly taking nutritional products that contain St. John's Wort
* Patients who underwent surgical treatment for endometriosis within 2 months prior to screening
* Patients who may need to regularly use analgesics for therapeutic objectives other than relief from the pain of dysmenorrhea during this study (occasional use permitted)

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With Intracyclic Bleeding at Cycle 6
outcomeMeasures.description: Intracyclic bleedings were defined as bleedings while a participant takes active tablets.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With a Change in Total Dysmenorrhea Score From Baseline to Cycle 6
outcomeMeasures.description: Total dysmenorrheal score was defined as sum of 2 sub-scores: severity of dysmenorrhea (none: 0, mild: 1, moderate: 2, severe: 3) and use of analgesics (none: 0, mild: 1, moderate: 2, severe: 3). Note: used with permission of Nobelpharma Co., Ltd. from the phase 3 clinical study protocol of IKH-01 in dysmenorrhea (associated with endometriosis) (Nobelpharma Co., Ltd.). Changed total dysmenorrheal scores: -6 to -1 mean improvement, 1 to 6 mean worsening, 0 means no change.

outcomeMeasures.title: Distribution of Total Dysmenorrhea Score at Cycle 6
outcomeMeasures.description: Total dysmenorrhea score was defined as sum of 2 sub-scores: severity of dysmenorrhea and use of analgesics. Higher score means it is more severe. 0=None, 6=Severest.

outcomeMeasures.description: Total dysmenorrhea score was defined as sum of 2 sub-scores: severity of dysmenorrhea and use of analgesics. Higher score means it is more severe. 0=None, 6=Severest.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Any Bleeding Episodes From Cycle 1 to Cycle 6
outcomeMeasures.description: Vaginal bleeding was rated as none, spotting, light, normal, or heavy based on the participant's experience. A reference period is about 3 cycles (90 days): reference period 1 is from Cycle 1 to Cycle 3 (the 1st 90 days), reference period 2 is from Cycle 4 to Cycle 6 (the 2nd 90 days).
